New Records: Adam Zampa became the third Australian spinner to take four wickets in a World Cup match
Key Match Events: Australia won the match by five wickets
Mitch Marsh was run out after making 52 runs
Josh Inglis scored his first World Cup 50
Glenn Maxwell contributed 28 runs in quick time
Pre-Game Insights: Australia were aiming to break their World Cup drought
Adam Zampa was managing a back injury
Post-Match Reflections: Adam Zampa was praised for his performance despite back spasms
The win lifted Australia's World Cup standings
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in Lucknow, India
The performance was live-streamed on Channel Nine
Others: The match was part of the 2023 Cricket World Cup
